This directory contains rules for the Linux udev daemon, installed into /etc/udev/rules.d. They
control the creation of device nodes for the various SDR front end devices.

Eventually the udev system will automatically invoke instances of radiod, the ka9q-radio spectrum server,
when a SDR front end device is plugged in. At the moment, each instance must be manually enabled with
systemctl (eg, sudo systemctl enable --now radiod@instance) and it will continually restart every
5 seconds until an appropriate SDR device is found.
